name: Overhead Triceps Extension (Barbell)
description: Targets the long head of the triceps by stretching and contracting through an overhead motion.

name: Skull Crusher (Barbell)
description: Isolates the triceps by lowering the barbell towards the forehead and extending upward.

name: Bench Dip
description: Strengthens the triceps by using body weight in a dipping motion with support from a bench.

name: Close-Grip Push-Up
description: Targets the triceps by narrowing hand placement during the push-up motion.

name: Skull Crusher (Dumbbell)
description: Isolates the triceps with dumbbells by lowering them towards the forehead and extending upward.

name: Overhead Triceps Extension (Dumbbell)
description: Focuses on the long head of the triceps by extending the dumbbell overhead.

name: Overhead Triceps Extension (Cable)
description: Uses a cable machine to focus on triceps extension with continuous resistance.

name: Triceps Bodyweight Extension
description: Uses body weight to target triceps in a plank position while extending the arms.

name: Triceps Pushdown With Bar
description: Targets triceps by pushing down a bar attached to a cable machine.

name: Triceps Pushdown With Rope
description: Engages triceps by pulling a rope attachment downward, focusing on arm extension.

name: Triceps Dip
description: Strengthens triceps through bodyweight dips using parallel bars.

name: Seated Dip Machine
description: Utilizes a machine to mimic the dip movement and isolate triceps.

name: Triceps Extension (Machine)
description: Isolates the triceps using a machine to control resistance during extension.

name: Triceps Kickback (Dumbbell)
description: Engages triceps by extending the arm backward with dumbbells in a bent-over position.

name: Triceps Kickback (Cable)

name: Triceps Dip (Assisted)
description: Uses assistance to help with dip exercises targeting triceps.

name: Close-Grip Bench Press
